LG Electronic has launched a free laundry service in Kano as part of a corporate social responsibility aimed at promoting hygiene in the state and the north west. The company s head of corporate marketing west Africa, Hari Krishna Elluru said the free wash centre is designed to operate on a daily basis in order to improve the living conditions as well as support the washing needs of the people of Kano. He said LG has served over over 25 000 people and waged over 190000 sets of clothes in other parts of the country where the free laundry is operating and hoped Kano will join immediately. He also said the facility is equipped with the state of art LG washing machine dryers, uninterrupted power and consistent water supply. Mr Jiung Park the General manager home appliances west Africa said the company is giving back to the society because the real beneficiaries are directly the people. ” For us, we believe life is good when shared with others.We remain competitive while improving sustainability our philosophy revolves around people ” he said. He explained that the free laundry service will be open from Monday to Saturdays 9am to 5pm and expects patronage from Kano.